ivardefs.name: address
ivardefs.desc: The uri that describes the actual end-point to connect to.

ivardefs.name: connectionType
ivardefs.desc: A coded value that represents the technical details of the usage of this endpoint, such as what WSDLs should be used in what way. (e.g. XDS.b/DICOM/cds-hook).

ivardefs.name: contact_
ivardefs.desc: Contact details for a human to contact about the subscription. The primary use of this for system administrator troubleshooting.

ivardefs.name: header_
ivardefs.desc: Additional headers / information to send as part of the notification.

ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: Identifier for the organization that is used to identify the endpoint across multiple disparate systems.

ivardefs.name: managingOrganization
ivardefs.desc: The organization that manages this endpoint (even if technically another organisation is hosting this in the cloud, it is the organisation associated with the data).

ivardefs.name: name
ivardefs.desc: A friendly name that this endpoint can be referred to with.

ivardefs.name: payloadMimeType_
ivardefs.desc: The mime type to send the payload in - e.g. application/fhir+xml, application/fhir+json. If the mime type is not specified, then the sender could send any content (including no content depending on the connectionType).

ivardefs.name: payloadType_
ivardefs.desc: The payload type describes the acceptable content that can be communicated on the endpoint.

ivardefs.name: period
ivardefs.desc: The interval during which the endpoint is expected to be operational.
